The paper discusses a distributed RDF system that addresses the challenges of partitioning and query optimization for very large RDF data. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on data partitioning and query optimization, cs.DB and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.IR, and cs.LG.
